We recommended that:

The Local Finance Committee and the Municipal Budget Office (MBO) as the lead office:


Enhance its current system of preparing the succeeding year’s revenue projections to come up with realistic targets that are backed up by current trends, verifiable figures and data;

Provide for the targets on income accounts that did not have projections which must be based on statistics, prior years’ experience and future expectation;

The Municipal Treasurer perform periodic review and collection monitoring to each revenue account especially to identify revenue sources which were not able to meet the targets; intensify collection strategies; institute appropriate action and make adjustments, when necessary; and


The Municipal Accounting Office coordinate with Municipal Treasurer’s Office to identify and use the correct account titles and codes per COA Circular 2015-009 (Revised Chart of Accounts for LGUs.

We recommended that the LCE:

Direct the concerned offices to reconcile their record and coordinate with each other to determine the status of completion of each PPAs. If applicable and with adequate supporting documents, the Municipal Accounting Office should make the necessary adjusting entries to reflect the correct presentation of account balances;

Instruct the concerned department head to implement immediately the projects/programs as agreed by both parties and as stated in the Memorandum of Agreement (MOA). The Municipality shall use the fund for specific purpose for which it was created, as stipulated in Section 309 of Republic Act (RA) No. 7160;

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to coordinate with the Department of Agriculture- National Meat Inspection Service (NMIS) about the Municipality’s unremitted collections to be remitted to that office; and



Require the Municipal Accountant to verify the validity of funds with long outstanding balances. Projects/programs should be terminated in accordance with the guidelines or agreement for which they were established and to return to the donor/source agency the unused balance upon accomplishment and termination of the program or project. If proven non-existing, request for write-off the said accounts to the COA.

